Actually, if you go to Layers-&gt;Colors-&gt;Colorcube Analysis, you can see the number of different colors in any image, whether the image is 8-bit or not. I just tested it with a photo that has about 25000 different colors. This is in version 2.2.10, so it may have been moved to a different menu in newer versions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=110">Josh</a> — Sun May 06, 2007 8:00 pm</p><hr />
