- No clues about the exact hardware procedure, though my emu runs 1 cycle of PPU, generates 1 background pixel (4 bits), it's ORed with color emphasis if required and transfered into a surface (bitmap). Once it's there, it can't be changed, since the palette is already loaded.<br /><br />- My question is... Let's assume it's correct. If I change the palette, it's possible to plot another pixel using another color. In other words, it's possible to display all the possible NES colors in a single frame...?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Mon Apr 30, 2007 4:03 pm</p><hr />
